The paper proposes a method for characterizing the framing of a given text by identifying relevant semantic axes using word embeddings. This involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves quantitative analysis of text data, which could fall under the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
